doc.after: Oversight on Wikipedia also known as suppression is a form of enhanced deletion which unlike normal deletion expunges information from any form of usual access even by administrators It is used within strict limits to remove defamatory material to protect privacy and sometimes to remove serious copyright violations from any page or log entry including if required the list of users on the English Wikipedia
